I **think** this is what the code would look like with BLOCK_ELASTICITY being changeable:
```ts
declare const BLOCK_ELASTICITY: number // multiplier on targetGas that represents the max gas a block can use; current spec says this is 2
declare const parentTargetGas: number
declare const parentGasUsed: number
declare const parentBaseFee: number
const parentGasUsedOverTarget = parentGasUsed - parentTargetGas // can be negative
if (parentGasUsedOverTarget > 0) {
    const newBaseFee = parentBaseFee + parentBaseFee / (8 * parentGasUsedOverTarget / parentTargetGas * (BLOCK_ELASTICITY - 1))
} else if (parentGasUsedOverTarget < 0) {
    const newBaseFee = parentBaseFee - parentBaseFee / (8 * Math.abs(parentGasUsedOverTarget) / parentTargetGas)
} else {
    const newBaseFee = parentBaseFee
}
```
